[
    {
        "content": "<p>For <code>linux/rust/</code> , is there a convention as to whether use <code>-</code> or <code>_</code> as a separator?</p>\n<p><code>rust/kernel/dma_buf/dma_fence.rs</code> vs <code>rust/kernel/dma-buf/dma-fence.rs</code></p>",
        "id": 604097691,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1781691679
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Use <a href=\"http://dma_fence.rs\">dma_fence.rs</a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://rust-lang.github.io/api-guidelines/naming.html\">https://rust-lang.github.io/api-guidelines/naming.html</a></p>",
        "id": 604098535,
        "sender_full_name": "Onur Özkan",
        "timestamp": 1781691861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>See the \"modules\" section in the link</p>",
        "id": 604098666,
        "sender_full_name": "Onur Özkan",
        "timestamp": 1781691888
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think you can even use kebab-case in modules at all, unless you use <code>#[path = ...]</code> attribute.</p>",
        "id": 604098951,
        "sender_full_name": "Manos Pitsidianakis",
        "timestamp": 1781691947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"1082757\">Manos Pitsidianakis</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/288089-General/topic/Path.20Naming.20Conventions/near/604098951\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don't think you can even use kebab-case in modules at all, unless you use <code>#[path = ...]</code> attribute.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Kebab-case <span aria-label=\"laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f606\" role=\"img\" title=\"laughing\">:laughing:</span> Never heard that before, but I like it <span aria-label=\"rolling on the floor laughing\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f923\" role=\"img\" title=\"rolling on the floor laughing\">:rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:</span></p>",
        "id": 604099719,
        "sender_full_name": "Andreas Hindborg",
        "timestamp": 1781692107
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yes, please use <code>_</code> (unless there is a good reason not to), for both module names and crate names.</p>",
        "id": 604100423,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1781692267
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Same applies to <code>path</code> and <code>crate_name</code> -- we try to only use them when there is a justification.</p>",
        "id": 604100602,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1781692307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>OK, already have it like that. Will keep, then</p>",
        "id": 604104374,
        "sender_full_name": "Philipp Stanner",
        "timestamp": 1781693153
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"692273\">Philipp Stanner</span> has marked this topic as resolved.</p>",
